	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64431140">It's just years and years later that they do it. In the past that wasn't an issue for the manufacturers because he destroyed most laptops so that they didn't have to worry about the used market. But modern CPUs and gpus are not getting any faster but they are getting cooler so laptops are lasting longer.<br> <br>

A surefire way to build obsolescence into your product so that you're not losing sales down the road is to solder in ram. This is especially true for Apple devices. <br> <br>

As an added bonus you can't just buy</div>
	</div>

